==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Septomaxillary
<hw>Sep`to*max"il*la*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the nasal septum and the
maxilla; situated in the region of these parts.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A small bone between the nasal septum and the
maxilla in many reptiles and amphibians.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Septuagenarian</ent>⟦br⟧
